      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode): show Zen balance for Go accounts without subscription usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- allow OpenCode Go accounts without Go subscription usage fields to fall back to the existing Zen balance fetch\n- render Zen-only accounts as balance-only snapshots instead of false 0% rate windows\n- reuse the Zen fallback when either the initial page precheck or final subscription parser rejects incomplete usage data\n- wait for required fallback data through the caller's full timeout while keeping the 250 ms grace only for optional enrichment\n- cancel the parallel balance task on unrelated failures and use synchronized request recording in concurrent tests\n- keep the existing parse error when neither Go subscription usage nor Zen balance is available\n\nFixes #1476\n\n## Tests\n- `swift test --filter OpenCodeGoUsageFetcherErrorTests --skip-update` (16 tests passed)\n- `make check` (SwiftFormat clean, SwiftLint 0 violations, packaging/release-path checks passed)\n- `git diff --check`\n- full-branch autoreview found two fallback gaps; both fixed\n- follow-up autoreview clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Proof and risk\n- one regression delays the Zen balance response beyond the optional 250 ms enrichment grace and verifies a balance-only snapshot still renders\n- another regression exercises a page that passes the initial rolling-usage precheck but fails final weekly/reset parsing\n- timeout assertions verify required fallback gets the caller's full timeout while successful subscription usage remains non-blocking\n- no live account or browser-cookie probe was run; repository policy requires explicit permission for live provider probes that may access browser or Keychain state\n- provider auth, cookie normalization, endpoints, and storage are unchanged",
        "branch": "kiran/opencode-zen-balance-only",
